> i'm still going for operator error in the checking procedure (ie, i'm 
> doing sumpin wrong), but what?

Turn crank ccw only for the gear backlash check.
Don't hold the cam.
Also hold crank, rock the cam , find the "click "
Anything else will require measurements.
V-blocks and dial the new crank.
Suspect the gearpress "operation".
( Failure to suspect new parts is wrong:)
